<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1485">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.12/20.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Brazilian Minister, Mexico City, reports that Archbishops of Guadalajara
                            and Monterey fear for safety of persons and properties themselves and
                            other Bishops in case Constitutionalists take Mexico City. Say to
                            Carranza that it is hoped he will order full <pb facs="1121" n="1005" xml:id="pg_1005"/> protection to be given persons and properties of
                            all persons connected with religious organizations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>